node.text:
This is a Western bush viper 🐍 Apply for a feature following the link in our bio and we will publish your photos in our account: @adventurefervor

African bush vipers are ambush predators, and commonly strike their prey while hanging upside down from a tree limb. There is no antivenom for this species of snake!

African bush vipers are commonly called “green vipers”, however they can be found in variations of red, orange, gray, yellow, black, blue, olive, and brown. They may also change color throughout their lifespan.

📽 @severus_snakes

node.text:
Apply for a feature following the link in our bio and we will publish your photos in our account: @adventurefervor

Naqshe Jahan Square in #Isfahan has been registered as a World Heritage Site by UNESCO. This historical square embraces some iconic monuments, one of them is Imam Mosque, it’s better to say the one of the most significant ones. This mosque is known also as Shah Mosque.
Imam Mosque is the best example of a thousand-year tradition in building mosques. The mosque is comprised of a main dome, two Shabestans (prayers hall), four porches, four minarets, and also including two seminaries next to the mosque to study theology.

The mosque was built near 400 years ago by the command of Shah Abbas I Safavi, Abbas the Great. The architecture and decorations of the mosque are really picturesque. One of the wonders of its architecture is the angle between the entrance and the main axis of the structure. The Propylaea is toward square to maintain the symmetry and harmony with the other buildings of square, while the structure of mosque is rotated toward Qibla. The wise and talented architect dissolved this rotation by combining some empty space in arch forms, and when you enter the mosque you don’t recognize a rotating plan.

Decorations of the Propylaea are really impressive, especially the magnificent tiles. When you want to enter the mosque, it’s better to take look above to shock. There is a perfect Muqarnas technique which has been decorated by the shrubs. Mihrab is the other significant part of the mosque.

📸 @fatemeghaderi

node.text:
Cherry blossoms in Japan 🌸💖✨ Wanna see your pictures posted in our account? Apply for a feature on adventurefervor.com (link in my bio: @adventurefervor)

Which one is your favorite, 1 to 10?

Looking for the best places to see cherry blossoms? Check out these 📝

1. Shinjuku Gyoen, Tokyo
2. Philosopher’s Path, Kyoto
3. Expo 70 Commemorative Park, Osaka
4. Nishi Park, Fukuoka
5. Takato Castle Park, Nagano
6. Mitsuike Park, Yokohama
7. Okayama Korakuen Garden, Okayama
8. Chureito Pagoda, Fuji Five Lakes
9. Miharu Takizakura, Fukushima
10. Mount Yoshino, Nara

Tag who you’d visit with!

📷 @number_shiiix
